FBIS3-8549 "dreeu049__a94004" FBIS-EEU-94-049-A Document Type:Daily Report 14 March 1994 ANNEX International Affairs Poland Offers To Send 150 Soldiers to Bosnia AU1003094094 Warsaw PAP in English 2330 GMT 9 Mar 94 AU1003094094 Warsaw PAP Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] New York, March 9 -- PAP has learned from British sources that Poland has offered to send an additional 150 soldiers to the former Yugoslavia. The decision was adopted in reply to an appeal of the UN secretary general calling for the strengthening of UNPROFOR [United Nations Protection Force] forces in Bosnia-Herzegovina. PAP has also learned that Polish General Jozef Chmiel will soon assume command of the northern sector of UNPROFOR. The Polish mission at the UN has not officially confirmed Poland's offer to send the additional soldiers.
